  "why": "PAPILLON explicitly enforces semantic consistency and naturalness during mutation by using LLM-driven, question-dependent mutators, system-prompt constraints, and perplexity/length controls so each generated mutant is coherent and realistic. However, the paper does not describe any mechanism that constrains or measures cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across multiple iterations (e.g., fixing semantically critical content or bounding similarity to the original seed). Mutations are produced per-step by the LLM helper and successful templates are added back to the seed pool for further evolution, which preserves per-mutation plausibility but can permit gradual drift over iterations. Therefore the method enforces plausibility per mutation step but does not demonstrate explicit controls to prevent cumulative drift, matching the definition of Medium.",
